---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../../components/PageHero.astro';
import { canonicalData, withBase } from '../../../lib/site-data.js';
---

<Layout
  title={`${canonicalData.site.title} | Flashcards Export`}
  description="How to import the generated flashcard TSV into Anki"
  currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}
>
  <PageHero
    kicker="Anki Export Guide"
    title="Import Flashcards Into Anki"
    description="Use the built-in TSV export from this static site, then import into Anki Desktop with tab separator and HTML enabled."
  />

  <section class="card section">
    <h2>Quick Steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>From <a href={withBase('/flashcards/')}>Flashcards</a>, export either all cards or your current filtered view.</li>
      <li>Open Anki Desktop and choose <strong>File -> Import</strong>.</li>
      <li>Select the downloaded <code>.tsv</code> file.</li>
      <li>Confirm separator is <strong>Tab</strong> (the file header also sets this automatically).</li>
      <li>Ensure HTML in fields is enabled so line breaks render from <code>&lt;br&gt;</code>.</li>
      <li>Verify columns map as: Front, Back, Tags, Deck.</li>
      <li>Import. Missing decks are created automatically from the deck column.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="card section">
    <h2>Included File Headers</h2>
    <pre>
#separator:Tab
#html:true
#columns:Front[tab]Back[tab]Tags[tab]Deck
#tags column:3
#deck column:4
    </pre>
    <p class="small">
      Note: The real file uses literal tab characters in the columns header. Fields are always quoted and newlines are
      converted to HTML line breaks for import reliability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section">
    <h2>Deck + Tags Behavior</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Deck base defaults to <code>CyberStudy</code> and can be customized on the export panel.</li>
      <li>Granularity options: one deck, by phase, or by week (default).</li>
      <li>Tags include original card tags plus computed metadata for phase/week/day/type/difficulty/exam.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  pre {
    padding: 0.8rem;
    border: 1px dashed var(--border);
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    white-space: pre-wrap;
  }
</style>

